HEADWORD: Schilling
<hw>Schil"ling</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[G. See
<er>Shilling</er>.]</ety> <def>Any one of several small German and Dutch
coins, worth from about one and a half cents to about five
